Craig McLaughlin is the Co-Founder, President and CEO of Extractable – an agency focused on digital solutions for wealth and health. Over the last two decades he and Extractable are proud to have driven successes for large-scale FIs, community banks, credit unions and fin-tech start-ups. Craig’s passion for using digital to drive and define financial experiences has earned him the reputation as an innovative and expert leader in Silicon Valley – and beyond. He is on a mission to positively impact the field of finance.  Craig holds a BSBA from San Diego State University and an M.S. in Information Systems & Web Technology from Hawaii Pacific University. When he’s not thinking about digital + finance, Craig loves spending time with his beautiful family and friends. He also enjoys wine, cycling and running – not necessarily in that order.

Craig was responsible for web technology solutions for various clients including CSAA, O'Reilly, WITI, and Logitech. In this technical positon Craig contributed to web architecture decisions and focused primarily on content management systems and XML integration.

Craig worked as a technical analyst for the Sony US Information Technology Research Center (USIRTC).  This small division of Sony based in the Silcon Valley was chartered with the intention of acting as internal consulting and research group within Sony Corporation.  The division reported directly the information technology group based on Tokyo.In this role Craig researched new technologies and presented both written and verbal communications that summarized the potential benefit to Sony as a whole.  Craig focused primarily on IP based technologies like XML and COM/DCOM.  This role included various consulting assignments for various global Sony divisions.
